Key Match Events: Australia posted 286 all out with Marnus Labuschagne top-scoring with 71 runs.
England managed 253 in reply, slumping to their sixth defeat.
Adam Zampa was player of the match for his stellar bowling figures of 3-21, including the wickets of Jos Buttler, Ben Stokes, and Moeen Ali.
Chris Woakes took 4-54, removing both Australian openers inside six overs.
Cameron Green scored 47 and Marcus Stoinis scored 35 to help Australia reach 286.
Jonny Bairstow fell for a first-ball duck, caught by Josh Inglis off Mitchell Starc.
Ben Stokes scored 64 and Dawid Malan scored 50 for England.
England's title defense ended when Ben Stokes was caught by Marcus Stoinis off Adam Zampa.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed disappointment and described the loss as a low point.
Pat Cummins praised his team's performance and their five-match winning streak.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad, India.
